      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WHISPERED (2) filled a minor placing last start at Geelong behind Jill's Juliette (26.16) in a Grade 5. Settled off speed and worked to the line nicely. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings two times from four attempts. One of the contenders. KING OF SNAKE (8) doesn't win out of turn but recent form sound. Has finished in the placings two on end now, the latest when third (42.50) at Sandown. Form here sound including four wins. Solid formlines coming through his last run. Can feature again. MAGIC SCOTCH (4) doesn't win out of turn but looks close to breaking through. Has hit the frame the last two runs, the latest when second (34.67) at this track. Will give a great sight again. REV GORDON (6) found the frame for the second consecutive time when narrowly beaten into third last time out (30.64) over 525m at this track.",
